      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-graph-surface"
        },
        "markdown": "## Graph surface checklist\n\nWhen a graph opens, ask:\n\n- What are the major node groups?\n- Which edges feel directional or structural?\n- Am I zoomed too far in to see the overall shape?\n- Would panning or the minimap help me re-center?\n- At this distance, am I looking for icon, summary, or detail surfaces?\n\nThe graph surface is part of the teaching model, not just a background.",
        "_placement": {
          "version": 1,
          "state": "auto-placed",
          "source": "layout",
          "updatedAt": 1781387326386,
          "reason": "auto-layout"
        }
      }
    },
